\displaystyle \frac{e^{-x}}{1-e^{-x}}
\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}e^{-kx}
\displaystyle \frac{e^{-x}}{1-e^{-x}}=\frac{1}{e^x-1}=\left(\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{x^k}{k!}-1\right)^{-1}=\left(\sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \frac{x^k}{k!}\right)^{-1}
\displaystyle\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{x^k}{k!}=e^x
